modules.description: Provides functions for capturing and injecting raw Ethernet frames, with support for BPF and AF_PACKET backends. Operates on byte sequences and Ethernet headers, enabling low-level network interaction. Used for tasks like crafting custom link-layer packets or implementing protocol analyzers without higher-layer abstractions.

Opens a raw network interface for sending and receiving full Ethernet frames, supporting BPF or AF_SOCKET backends. Processes packets using Cstruct.t, enabling low-level network interactions like DHCP communication. Provides filters for capturing DHCP client and server traffic on specific ports.
